es as a more realistic\nexample of its use; performance and versatility are highlighted, and\ntheoretical and numerical advantages over existing methods, as well as possible\nfuture improvements, are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Apr 2019 17:59:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 2 Nov 2019 16:54:32 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 5 Nov 2019 09:53:23 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 14 May 2020 16:44:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-20"}
