acuum and the\nstrangeness can be as abundant as up- and down-quarks at the core of two-solar\nmass neutron stars. Within our modeling the maximum mass is found less than\n~2.35 times solar mass and the baryon density at the core ranges in ~5-8n0.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Apr 2019 09:20:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 May 2019 12:07:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-04"}
